TableContextTimeStampAfterTable: {186109=Cheney, WA 99004-2476, 186196=Fax: (509) 359-2828, 30954=HS: Graduated from Jesuit HS in Carmichael, Calif., in 2009. He was a two-year starter as a defensive back and wide receiver, but had to sit out his senior season following knee surgery. He also played as a running back, kicker, punt returner and kickoff returner. In one game, he had 180 all-purpose yards, a rushing touchdown, an interception return for a TD and six tackles. Twice he was named his team’s defensive MVP and earned the Coaches Award as a freshman. He also earned two letters in basketball and was his team’s defensive MVP. In track and field, he competed in the 200 and 400 meters, as well as the 4x100 and 4x400 relays. He was a member of the Christian Leadership Council, Feed the Hungry, Chess Club and Black Student Union at Jesuit., 186159=Phone: (509) 359-2463, 30424=Kentucky: Transferred from Kentucky and attended EWU for the first time in fall 2012. Redshirted in 2009, played in one game in 2010 and did not see any game action in 2011. He had one tackle in his lone game against Akron in his sophomore season, and earned defensive scout team player of the week honors for that game. He was also on “special forces” for the Louisville game. His community service endeavors at Kentucky included his participation in the Fair Trade Festival.}
